{{Infobox Shinto shrine
| religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]]
| image                 = File:Susa-jinja-honden.jpg
}}
Susa Shrine is a [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Shimane Prefecture]], [[Izumo, Shimane]]. It is a [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Izumo, Shimane]]. It is the 18th Shinto shrine in Izumo Province.

The main deity is [[Susanoo-no-Mikoto|Susanoo-no-Mikoto]], and his wife, [[Kushinadahime|Inada-hime]], and Inada-hime's parents, Ashimazuchi-no-mikoto and Temazuchi-no-mikoto, are also enshrined.{{Efn|It is said that the three deities were enshrined at the shrine site on the opposite side of the Susa River (currently on the grounds of Yukari-kan) until the [[Tenbun]] period.}}。{{citation needed}}

