{{Nihongo|{{ill|Susa Shrine|ja|須佐神社 (出雲市)}}|須佐神社|Susa Jinja}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Shimane Prefecture]], [[Izumo, Shimane]]. It is a [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Izumo, Shimane]]. It is the 18th Shinto shrine in Izumo Province.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=須佐神社 |url=https://thegate12.com/tw/spot/934 |access-date=2022-06-27 |website=THE GATE}}</ref>
The main deity is [[Susanoo-no-Mikoto|Susanoo-no-Mikoto]], and his wife, [[Kushinadahime|Inada-hime]], and [[Kushinadahime|Inada-hime's]] parents, {{Interlanguage link|Ashinazuchi and Tenazuchi|lt=Ashimazuchi-no-mikoto|ja|アシナヅチ・テナヅチ}} and {{Interlanguage link|Ashinazuchi and Tenazuchi|lt=Temazuchi-no-mikoto|ja|アシナヅチ・テナヅチ}}, are also enshrined.{{Efn|It is said that the three deities were enshrined at the shrine site on the opposite side of the Susa River (currently on the grounds of Yukari-kan) until the [[Tenbun]] period.}}。<ref name=":0" />
== History == The shrine was founded in 776<ref name=":2">{{Cite web |title=須佐神社｜出雲観光ガイド【出雲観光協会公式ホームページ】 |url=https://www.izumo-kankou.gr.jp/684 |access-date=2022-06-27 |website=出雲観光ガイド【出雲観光協会公式ホームページ】 |language=jp}}</ref>
The priests of the shrine are said to be descendants of [[Ōkuninushi]]<ref>{{Ill|Tanigawa Ken'ichi|de}} 『日本の神々 神社と聖地 7 山陰』（新装復刊） 2000年 白水社 ISBN 978-4-560-02507-9</ref>
It is mentioned in the [[Engishiki]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |title=須佐神社{{!}}ヤマタノオロチ伝説とゆかりの地{{!}}出雲神話とゆかりの地{{!}}縁結びパワースポットと出雲神話{{!}}島根浪漫旅 |url=https://www.izumo-shinwa.com/spot_dtl_susa.html |access-date=2022-06-27 |website=www.izumo-shinwa.com}}</ref>
== Description == It has a 1300-year-old [[Shinboku|sacred tree]]<ref name=":1" />
